    <!-- Application Structure Plan: A single-page, scrolling dashboard design with a sticky navigation bar. The structure follows a compelling narrative: 1. Hero/Intro, 2. The specific Challenge in Indonesia (now with military-specific data), 3. Evolution of ECG Diagnostics, 4. The AI Solution (AiTiA), 5. Interactive Product Showcase with comparison charts, 6. Clinical Evidence/Credibility, 7. Strong Points of Our Product, 8. Military Health (new integrated section), 9. Pipeline, 10. Global Roadmap & Commitment, 11. Business Model, 12. The Indonesian Opportunity summary, and 13. Contact. This structure was chosen to guide stakeholders from problem to solution to proof, making a complex proposal easily digestible and persuasive, which is more effective than a linear slide-by-slide presentation. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 1. Heart Failure Comparison: Goal=Compare, Viz=Bar Chart (Chart.js), Interaction=Hover for tooltips. Justification=Directly visualizes the superior AUROC of AiTiA LVSD vs. Blood Test. 2. Heart Attack Comparison: Goal=Compare, Viz=Bar Chart (Chart.js), Interaction=Hover. Justification=Illustrates AiTiA MI's outperformance of physicians, as stated in the report. 3. Outpatient HF Comparison: Goal=Compare, Viz=Bar Chart (Chart.js), Interaction=Hover. Justification=Shows the power of the smartwatch solution vs. traditional tests. Other elements like icons and styled cards are used to visually break up text and improve readability, presenting key data points (e.g., mortality rates, publications) in a high-impact way. Challenge data now includes military-specific details. "Strong Points" and "Opportunity" sections explicitly detail benefits for military healthcare and combat readiness. Heart muscle comparison and AI workflow are represented using unicode characters and Tailwind CSS for visual emphasis without external image files. The "Evolution of ECG" and "Pipeline" sections use structured HTML/CSS for process and tabular data. New "Military Health" section integrates content from the dedicated military page. CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
